<plot>It's so very simple. Red on white. Two vertical bars, and between them a single maple leaf. For Canadians under 40, it has always been our flag. Nothing else says, as simply and as clearly, "We are Canadian." But the birth of Canada's flag in 1965 was anything but simple. It pitted two of Canada's greatest leaders against one another in a thunderous clash.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?010428</url></doc>
